I would like to know how do you perform element-wise comparison of two matrix ?

## Expected Behavior

I expected to following behavior

dlib::matrix<double,3,1> m1; 
m1 = 1,1,1;
dlib::matrix<double,3,1> m2;
m2 = 2,2,2;
m1 <= m2 returns vector 1,1,1 (i.e. element-wise comparison)
m1 <= 2 return vector 1,1,1 (i.e. element-wise comparison)

## Current Behavior

But I currently have the following behavior

dlib::matrix<double,3,1> m1; 
m1 = 1,1,1;
dlib::matrix<double,3,1> m2;
m2 = 2,2,2;
m1 <= m2 returns true (i.e. full comparison)
m1 <= 2 return a vector 1,1,1 (i.e. element-wise comparison)

Idem for the over comparison operators.

